        <div class="card-body">
            <h2><code>GetMessageSignature</code></h2>
            <br />
            <h4>Description</h4>
            <p>
                This endpoint generates a signature for a user-provided file and packs it into a zip archive along with the original file and the signature file.
            </p>
            <br />
            <h4>Endpoint</h4>

            <h4><strong><code>POST /api/purefile/GetMessageSignature</code></strong></h4>
            <br />
            <h4>Request Body</h4>
            <p>The request body should be of type <b>'multipart/form-data'</b> and contain the following fields:</p>
            <div class="table-responsive">
                <table class="table table-bordered table-hover">
                    <thead>
                        <tr style="text-align:center; background-color: gray">
                            <th style="color: #fff">Field</th>
                            <th style="color: #fff">Type</th>
                            <th style="color: #fff">Description</th>
                        </tr>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <tr style="text-align: center;">
                            <td>userFile</td>
                            <td>file</td>
                            <td>The user-provided file to be signed.</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr style="text-align:center;">
                            <td>privateKeyFile</td>
                            <td>.key file</td>
                            <td>The private key file for signing.</td>
                        </tr>
                    </tbody>
                </table>
            </div>
            <br />
            <h4>Responses</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <b>200 OK:</b>
                    Returns the verification result.
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            Content-Type: application/zip
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Body: The zip file containing the original file and its signature. <br />
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <b>400 Bad Request:</b>
                    If either the user file or the private key file is missing.
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            Content-Type: application/problem+json
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Body: Error message
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <b>500 Internal Server Error:</b>
                    If an error occurs during signature generation or zip file creation.
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            Content-Type: application/problem+json
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Body: Error message
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
            </ul>
            <br />
            <h4>Example</h4><br />
            <h5>Request</h5>
            <h5><strong><code style="color:green">POST /api/purefile/GetMessageSignature</code></strong></h5>
            <h5><strong><code style="color:green">Content-Type: multipart/form-data</code></strong></h5>
            <br />
            <br />
            <h5><strong><code style="color:green">userFile: [file content] </code></strong></h5>
            <h5><strong><code style="color:green">privateKeyFile: [file content] </code></strong></h5>
            <br />
            <h5>Response</h5>
            <code>
                Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="SignedFiles.zip"<br />
                Content-Type: application/zip
            </code>
            <br />
            <br />
            <h4>Notes</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>The signature is generated using the FalconWrapper library with a logarithm value of 10.</li>
                <li>Both the user file and the private key file are required for signature generation.</li>
                <li>If either the user file or the private key file is missing, a bad request error will be returned.</li>
                <li>If an error occurs during signature generation or zip file creation, an error message will be returned.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

